<section class="overview">
  <h2>The Four BSA Bases</h2>

  <div class="benefits">
    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>Philmont Scout Ranch (New Mexico)</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Backpacking</p>
      <p>50-100+ mile treks in the Sangre de Cristo Mountains at 6,000-12,000 ft elevation.</p>
      <p><strong>Age:</strong> 14+ | <strong>Cost:</strong> ~$1,000-1,200</p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>Northern Tier (Minnesota)</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Wilderness canoeing</p>
      <p>Boundary Waters expeditions paddling 50-150 miles. Also offers Okpik winter camping.</p>
      <p><strong>Age:</strong> 14+ | <strong>Cost:</strong> ~$850-950</p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>Florida Sea Base</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Water adventures</p>
      <p>Scuba, sailing, and island camping in the Florida Keys and Bahamas.</p>
      <p><strong>Age:</strong> 13+ | <strong>Cost:</strong> ~$550-750</p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefit">
      <h3>Summit Bechtel Reserve (West Virginia)</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Activity sampler</p>
      <p>Climbing, mountain biking, rafting, ziplines, and more.</p>
      <p><strong>Age:</strong> 14+ | <strong>Cost:</strong> ~$450-600</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

